      • calculatePartSize

        public static long calculatePartSize(long contentLength,
                                     long minPartSize)
        Calculate a proper size of multipart piece. If minPartSize is too small, the number of multipart pieces may exceed the limit of Constants.MULTIPART_UPLOAD_PART_NUM_LIMIT.
        Parameters:
        contentLength - the size of file.
        minPartSize - the minimum size of multipart piece.
        Returns:
        a revisional size of multipart piece.

      • getMultipartSizeProperty

        public static long getMultipartSizeProperty(org.apache.hadoop.conf.Configuration conf,
                                            String property,
                                            long defVal)
        Get a size property from the configuration: this property must be at least equal to Constants.MULTIPART_MIN_SIZE. If it is too small, it is rounded up to that minimum, and a warning printed.
        Parameters:
        conf - configuration
        property - property name
        defVal - default value
        Returns:
        the value, guaranteed to be above the minimum size
